The paper presents a learning-based framework for medical image registration using convolutional neural networks. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of auxiliary segmentations and optimization techniques, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper focuses on medical image analysis and processing, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) category.
